        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 3:35PM PDT by NWS Pendleton OR</headline>
        <description>At 334 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Dixie, or 8 miles east of Walla Walla, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dixie, Kooskooskie, Ski Bluewood, and Walla Walla.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
